text.__SUMMARY__:
Baeckea pachyphylla is a shrub found along the south coast Western Australia.The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.4 to 1 metre (1.3 to 3.3 ft). It blooms between September and January producing pink and white flowers.
It is found on sand plains and gentle slopes the Great Southern and south western coastal parts of Goldfields-Esperance region of Western Australia where it grows in sandy, clay and loamy soils around granite.
